# React TSX port

`*.tsx` files are the React runtime beside `*.templ`. Both are thin
implementations of the same `*.spec.md` + `*.variants.json` contract.

See [`docs/architecture.md`](../../docs/architecture.md) and
[`docs/coming-from-shadcn.md`](../../docs/coming-from-shadcn.md).

## Layout grammar (applies to TSX too)

The Templ layout grammar is binding on the React side as well. See
[`templ-layout-grammar.mdc`](templ-layout-grammar.mdc).

- `Block` opens every block exactly once per file and carries the landmark `tag`.
- `Box` lives only inside `Block` (or another layout primitive).
- `Stack` is vertical flex; `Group` is horizontal flex (or `fieldset`).
- No raw markup (`<div>`, `<aside>`, `<section>`, …) inside `ui/`, `components/`,
  or example blocks when a primitive or composite exists.

## Variants and class composition

- `cva: true` props map to literal unions via `RecipeKey<typeof recipe, K>`.
- `composeRecipe<R>(recipe, selection, ...extra)` is generic; never cast with
  `as VariantRecipe`.
- `*.variants.json` is the only source of truth for variant class strings; do
  not duplicate recipes in TS.
- `cn` = `clsx + tailwind-merge`; caller `className` wins over recipe classes.
- Empty-string variant keys are forbidden. `defaults[k]` must reference a real
  key in `byKey[k]`.

## Composition primitives

- Clickable bricks that delegate their semantic root support `asChild` via the
  shared `Slot`: `Button`, `SheetTrigger`, `SheetClose`, and future triggers
  when the spec documents it.
- `asChild` merges `className` and event handlers onto the single child
  (Radix-style). Use it for `<a>` wrapped as a button.
- TSX uses `htmlFor`/`target` (or other neutral names), not `for`. The Go
  `For string` field stays unchanged.
- Card uses named exports only (`CardHeader`, `CardTitle`, ...). Do not add
  compound dot APIs such as `Card.Header`.

## Behavior bricks

- **`Sheet`** (side panel): declarative markup only. Set `behavior="ui8kit"`
  and wire `target` / `For` ids. `@ui8kit/aria` owns open/close on both stacks.
  Root is `<div role="dialog">`, not native `<dialog>`.
- When `Sheet behavior="ui8kit"` is active, `open` is initial SSR state only.
  React must not use controlled state to own runtime visibility.
- **`Dialog`** (center modal): exposes `open?: boolean` and
  `onOpenChange?: (open: boolean) => void` for native `<dialog>` control.
- `behavior?: "ui8kit"` is **opt-in** on Sheet parts. When set, bricks emit
  `data-ui8kit-*` hooks matching `.templ` markup exactly.
- Custom JS pattern implementations are forbidden — see
  [`docs/aria.md`](../../docs/aria.md).

## Dependencies

- `ui/` and `components/` MUST NOT import npm packages beyond `react` and
  `clsx`/`tailwind-merge` (the `cn` helpers).
- `react`, `clsx`, and `tailwind-merge` are `peerDependencies`, not bundled.
- Behavior is opt-in via `behavior="ui8kit"`; do not pull `@ui8kit/aria` into
  bricks. The app registers the pattern subset it ships.

## Imports

- Inside the registry use relative paths (`../../utils`, `../slot/slot`).
- Inside `examples/vite` use the `@registry/ui` and `@registry/components`
  aliases only. Do not mix deep relative imports with aliases in the same file.

## Validation

- `bun run typecheck:react` must pass.
- `bun run lint:ui8px` covers `ui/`, `components/`, `utils/`, and `examples/`
  including `examples/vite/src/**/*.tsx`.
- `bun run validate:aria` covers `examples/` markup against the registered
  `@ui8kit/aria` manifest.
- Specs may declare `targets.react.test`; when present, `validate-spec` requires
  the referenced `.test.tsx` or `.test.ts` file to exist.
